Barclays Puts Israeli Shekel Debt on Global Aggregate Index

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-10-03T14:24:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/barclays-puts-israeli-shekel-debt-on-global-aggregate-index.html
Barclays Capital  said Israeli shekel-
denominated debt will also be eligible for the Global Aggregate
Index from Jan. 1.  The debt will continue to be part of the Local Currency
Emerging Markets Bond Index. The decision was made after careful
evaluation of “the evolving fixed income landscape,” Barclays
said in an e-mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  